00:02:23.450 --> 00:02:27.530
So we're going to talk today
about genius, I believe.

00:02:27.530 --> 00:02:28.237
Is that correct?

00:02:28.237 --> 00:02:30.320
The title of the talk is
the technology of genius?

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:33.005
Is that how was it was labeled?

00:02:33.005 --> 00:02:34.380
We're going to
talk about genius.

00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:38.030
Actually, I feel like
genius is a topic

00:02:38.030 --> 00:02:44.110
we don't want to get too
defined about, too comfortable

00:02:44.110 --> 00:02:44.650
about it.

00:02:44.650 --> 00:02:46.110
It's an ongoing investigation.

00:02:46.110 --> 00:02:48.610
So actually in the
drive down in the car

00:02:48.610 --> 00:02:50.830
while my friend, Jonathan,
was behind the wheel,

00:02:50.830 --> 00:02:54.360
I was coming up with
my latest version

00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:57.220
of my understanding of genius.

00:02:57.220 --> 00:02:59.970
So I think of genius
as the capacity

00:02:59.970 --> 00:03:04.810
to express things that
are new, the capacity

00:03:04.810 --> 00:03:08.670
to bring forth ideas, an
embodiment of those ideas

00:03:08.670 --> 00:03:12.640
in a way that's not been
done before, but in a way

00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:16.500
that is aligned with
the collective solution

00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:18.350
of humanity.

00:03:18.350 --> 00:03:19.250
See the point?

00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:21.850
Because you can come up with
new ideas and new thoughts.

00:03:21.850 --> 00:03:23.704
But if it's completely
skewed with to where

00:03:23.704 --> 00:03:25.120
way the rest of
humanity is going,

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:27.130
no one's going to
take any notice.

00:03:27.130 --> 00:03:30.890
So an example, one of the
most obvious examples to me

00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:35.330
of genius is Nicolaus
Copernicus, who

00:03:35.330 --> 00:03:38.880
founded Dell computer
I think, was it?

00:03:38.880 --> 00:03:41.980
Nicolaus Copernicus back
in the 16th century,

00:03:41.980 --> 00:03:43.960
he had just the idea.

00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:48.480
It began just with an
inkling that perhaps there

00:03:48.480 --> 00:03:53.560
was a way to explain the
erratic behavior of the planets.

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:56.130
It appeared at that
time that the planets

00:03:56.130 --> 00:03:57.880
were like billiard
balls just going

00:03:57.880 --> 00:04:01.680
in bizarre directions at the
whim of some kind of creator

00:04:01.680 --> 00:04:03.320
with ADD.

00:04:03.320 --> 00:04:05.030
And it was Nicolaus
Copernicus who

00:04:05.030 --> 00:04:07.420
thought that maybe it could
be the other way around.

00:04:07.420 --> 00:04:09.200
Maybe, in fact,
instead of everything

00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:12.660
going around the earth in a
completely unintelligible way,

00:04:12.660 --> 00:04:15.659
maybe, in fact, we
like the other planets,

00:04:15.659 --> 00:04:16.700
are going around the sun.

00:04:16.700 --> 00:04:20.060
Which suddenly,
everything made sense.

00:04:20.060 --> 00:04:25.710
Copernicus' discovery was
not only about astronomy.

00:04:25.710 --> 00:04:27.550
It was about things
making sense.

00:04:27.550 --> 00:04:31.350
Was about a universe that
actually was intelligible.

00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:36.910
And this gave rise to
shifts in humanitarian,

00:04:36.910 --> 00:04:39.200
in art, in architecture.

00:04:39.200 --> 00:04:42.660
And all kinds of
fields were transformed

00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:45.330
through this shift
in understanding.

00:04:45.330 --> 00:04:46.990
So that's an example of genius.

00:04:46.990 --> 00:04:50.020
Somebody who had the right
idea at the right time,

00:04:50.020 --> 00:04:55.430
but it was aligned with the
next shift for humanity anyway.

00:04:55.430 --> 00:04:58.660
So in a way, the same
thing is true of where

00:04:58.660 --> 00:05:00.095
we are sitting today.

00:05:00.095 --> 00:05:04.020
Or where I'm standing today,
and you're sitting today.

00:05:04.020 --> 00:05:09.380
Years ago, Larry and Sergey
had an idea originally,

00:05:09.380 --> 00:05:14.660
an idea of how we could find
information in the emerging web

00:05:14.660 --> 00:05:16.420
more efficiently, more easily.

00:05:16.420 --> 00:05:20.390
And it's turned into probably
the most successful technology

00:05:20.390 --> 00:05:22.660
company in the world.

00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:24.680
So what is genius?

00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:26.880
What is it that allows
some people to have

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:31.830
the right idea at the right
time that just takes off

00:05:31.830 --> 00:05:34.040
and is picked up everybody.

00:05:34.040 --> 00:05:36.990
And what is it that
causes other people to be

00:05:36.990 --> 00:05:40.360
in a different disposition,
one more of cooperation

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:42.255
with those ideas,
or following ideas.

00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:47.790
And sometimes which could
to a feeling of frustration,

00:05:47.790 --> 00:05:52.040
or that there's more to
my life than I'm living.

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:56.330
So what is the
mechanism of genius?

00:05:56.330 --> 00:06:03.320
What is it that allows
this mysterious click

00:06:03.320 --> 00:06:06.960
to happen when you're tapped
into something way bigger

00:06:06.960 --> 00:06:09.940
than the conditioning
of your own mind?

00:06:09.940 --> 00:06:11.550
That's really been
the question that

00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:17.850
has governed my entire
adult life, from being

00:06:17.850 --> 00:06:19.470
a student at
Cambridge University.

00:06:19.470 --> 00:06:23.000
That was really what fascinated
me more than anything else.

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:26.270
What is it that allows
us-- well first of all,

00:06:26.270 --> 00:06:29.370
what is it allows us to live
incredibly fulfilled lives?

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:32.700
What is the key that allows
some people under almost

00:06:32.700 --> 00:06:36.600
any circumstance to be
living a life of no regret,

00:06:36.600 --> 00:06:39.030
to be living a life where
you're impassioned, where you're

00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:42.350
on fire, where you
feel grateful easily.

00:06:42.350 --> 00:06:44.730
And what is it that
allows many other people

00:06:44.730 --> 00:06:47.999
to be suffering, not always
for physical reasons,

00:06:47.999 --> 00:06:49.540
but especially in
our culture, people

00:06:49.540 --> 00:06:52.560
suffer more for
psychological reasons,

00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:55.180
for attitudinal
reasons more them

00:06:55.180 --> 00:06:57.330
because they don't
have enough food

00:06:57.330 --> 00:07:03.210
or water, or physical things.

00:07:03.210 --> 00:07:05.670
Initially in this
investigation, I

00:07:05.670 --> 00:07:08.470
thought that
ultimate fulfillment

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:12.090
was to do with spirituality.

00:07:12.090 --> 00:07:15.480
Because a lot of the most
fulfilled people in our culture

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:18.230
have been mystics,
have been people

00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:23.070
who have created spiritual
traditions or religions.

00:07:23.070 --> 00:07:24.760
But actually, when
we investigate it

00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:27.300
in an objective way,
it's not always true.

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:30.030
You can make your life
about spirituality.

00:07:30.030 --> 00:07:32.340
You can make your
life about meditation.

00:07:32.340 --> 00:07:34.795
Doesn't necessarily,
in a reliable way,

00:07:34.795 --> 00:07:36.740
lead to fulfillment.

00:07:36.740 --> 00:07:38.830
So what else could it be?

00:07:38.830 --> 00:07:41.320
Then I considered
maybe it's love.

00:07:41.320 --> 00:07:43.810
Maybe it's having
perfect relationships,

00:07:43.810 --> 00:07:48.150
having the right spouse,
and the right 2.35 children,

00:07:48.150 --> 00:07:49.940
in the right suburb
of the right city.

00:07:49.940 --> 00:07:52.740
Maybe that's the
key to fulfillment.

00:07:52.740 --> 00:07:55.250
We don't have so long to go
into all the possibilities.

00:07:55.250 --> 00:07:57.170
And there are many
possible answers.

00:07:57.170 --> 00:08:00.980
But what seems to hit
the nail every time

00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:04.830
is to drop into the
frequency of genius.

00:08:04.830 --> 00:08:08.470
When we fall into, as
Rachel was speaking,

00:08:08.470 --> 00:08:11.622
when we fall into a
flow where you know

00:08:11.622 --> 00:08:13.170
you're doing the right thing.

00:08:13.170 --> 00:08:16.800
You know you're creating
the right thing.

00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:19.350
You know that you're
contributing exactly what you

00:08:19.350 --> 00:08:21.900
were born to contribute,
to contribute

00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:24.160
to all of us moving forwards.

00:08:24.160 --> 00:08:25.970
That I would say,
whenever someone

00:08:25.970 --> 00:08:30.410
falls into that frequency,
it's a reliable key

00:08:30.410 --> 00:08:35.600
to a life of no regret, to a
life of complete fulfillment.

00:08:35.600 --> 00:08:39.890
So I want to talk to you here
about some essential keys

00:08:39.890 --> 00:08:41.630
that I've discovered
in investigating

00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:45.240
this my whole life,
essential keys which,

00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:49.940
each one on their own, may not
be the reliable key to genius.

00:08:49.940 --> 00:08:52.300
But when we bring
these keys together,

00:08:52.300 --> 00:08:55.370
I would say they provide
the most reliable,

00:08:55.370 --> 00:08:59.410
the most predictable soil
to bring forth genius.

00:08:59.410 --> 00:09:02.709
And before we go
into the keys, I

00:09:02.709 --> 00:09:04.250
want to make an
important distinction

00:09:04.250 --> 00:09:09.620
for all of us between
meme and method.

00:09:09.620 --> 00:09:11.580
We're familiar
with the word meme.

00:09:11.580 --> 00:09:13.389
Does it jive for you?

00:09:13.389 --> 00:09:14.180
AUDIENCE: Oh, yeah.

00:09:14.180 --> 00:09:14.590
ARJUNA ARDAGH: Oh, yeah.

00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:15.470
Big time.

00:09:15.470 --> 00:09:18.790
OK so what I mean, what
I understand by a meme

00:09:18.790 --> 00:09:21.570
is a commonly
shared understanding

00:09:21.570 --> 00:09:26.570
about things which doesn't
particularly belong to anybody.

00:09:26.570 --> 00:09:30.220
So a great example
would be electricity,

00:09:30.220 --> 00:09:32.580
where electricity
is a principle.

00:09:32.580 --> 00:09:35.090
Once we understand that
if you've got cables,

00:09:35.090 --> 00:09:40.462
and you got metal, and you
can vibrate-- my physics

00:09:40.462 --> 00:09:42.920
is probably a little shaky to
really explain this properly.

00:09:42.920 --> 00:09:45.610
When you could vibrate atoms
at a certain frequency,

00:09:45.610 --> 00:09:47.760
it will be carried
along a piece of metal

00:09:47.760 --> 00:09:50.100
and create energy that can
be moved from one place

00:09:50.100 --> 00:09:50.600
to another.

00:09:50.600 --> 00:09:52.391
Is that that-- did I
do a hash job of that,

00:09:52.391 --> 00:09:54.430
or is it in the right ballpark?

00:09:54.430 --> 00:09:56.020
So electricity would
be a meme, right?

00:09:56.020 --> 00:09:57.610
It doesn't belong to anybody.

00:09:57.610 --> 00:10:00.160
Once we understand
it, it's universal.

00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:02.745
The light bulb, invented
by Thomas Edison,

00:10:02.745 --> 00:10:03.495
would be a method.

00:10:03.495 --> 00:10:09.440
It's a method to be
able to use a meme.

00:10:09.440 --> 00:10:13.160
If we get too caught
up in methods,

00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:15.550
we become essentially consumers.

00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:19.360
If you get too caught up
in loyalty to methods,

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:21.750
then you become a consumer
of General Electric,

00:10:21.750 --> 00:10:23.950
the company founded
by Thomas Edison.

00:10:23.950 --> 00:10:25.470
And you forget the meme.

00:10:25.470 --> 00:10:28.730
The meme, when you have
an understanding of meme,

00:10:28.730 --> 00:10:30.420
it opens up possibilities.

00:10:30.420 --> 00:10:33.680
When a meme becomes yours,
you become the creator

00:10:33.680 --> 00:10:37.060
of methods instead of
the follower of methods.

00:10:37.060 --> 00:10:39.650
So I want to
introduce to you today

00:10:39.650 --> 00:10:42.340
seven important
memes that I would

00:10:42.340 --> 00:10:45.770
say if you can find
a way in your own way

00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:48.880
to embody these, to play with
them, to experiment with them,

00:10:48.880 --> 00:10:53.820
it's going to radically increase
your genius quota in your life,

00:10:53.820 --> 00:10:55.950
starting today.

00:10:55.950 --> 00:10:58.034
Does that sound like a plan?

00:10:58.034 --> 00:10:59.200
Three people is good for me.

00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:01.260
OK.

00:11:01.260 --> 00:11:07.310
So the first principle,
reliable principle,

00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:13.990
which brings forth genius I
would call inspired certainty.

00:11:13.990 --> 00:11:17.160
And I don't mean that
you necessarily initially

00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:22.340
are inspired with certainty
about your own ideas.

00:11:22.340 --> 00:11:26.240
Inspired certainty
refers to the influence

00:11:26.240 --> 00:11:29.140
that someone else
can have on you

00:11:29.140 --> 00:11:34.390
to be able to see through
your conditioned thoughts,

00:11:34.390 --> 00:11:37.270
through your reactive feelings
which very often dominate

00:11:37.270 --> 00:11:41.730
our behavior, to see
into the essence of you,

00:11:41.730 --> 00:11:47.110
and to say I see you in there.

00:11:47.110 --> 00:11:49.500
Beyond the habits
you've learned,

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:51.310
I see who you really are.

00:11:51.310 --> 00:11:55.930
I see the gift that is
a waiting to be born.

00:11:55.930 --> 00:11:59.510
When I was 14 years old, I
went to a boarding school

00:11:59.510 --> 00:12:01.210
in England.

00:12:01.210 --> 00:12:03.180
The closest thing you
have to that America

00:12:03.180 --> 00:12:04.013
is the penitentiary.

00:12:06.340 --> 00:12:08.420
So I went to an
English boarding school

00:12:08.420 --> 00:12:13.450
where I had an English teacher,
whose name was Mr. Coleman.

00:12:13.450 --> 00:12:19.290
And he was like Santa Claus,
but with actually a dark beard

00:12:19.290 --> 00:12:20.000
instead of white.

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:21.500
But he had a big,
[INAUDIBLE] beard.

00:12:21.500 --> 00:12:22.510
He was a big man.

00:12:22.510 --> 00:12:26.876
And he loved great literature.

00:12:26.876 --> 00:12:28.750
So he would give us
every week, he would say,

00:12:28.750 --> 00:12:31.210
just write from your experience.

00:12:31.210 --> 00:12:32.510
Write from what excites you.

00:12:32.510 --> 00:12:34.280
Write from what you're
passionate about.

00:12:34.280 --> 00:12:36.170
So I would go and do that.

00:12:36.170 --> 00:12:39.170
And I would take him back
my essay, written of course

00:12:39.170 --> 00:12:44.670
in squiggly fountain pen because
we didn't have computers then.

00:12:44.670 --> 00:12:49.140
We also didn't have
cars or-- my son

00:12:49.140 --> 00:12:52.505
is sitting here in the audience,
and he sometimes asks me,

00:12:52.505 --> 00:12:53.880
Dad-- when he was
young, he said,

00:12:53.880 --> 00:12:55.880
Dad did they have cars
when you were growing up?

00:12:58.730 --> 00:13:00.010
So no computers.

00:13:00.010 --> 00:13:03.660
So I was writing my
essay with a pen.

00:13:03.660 --> 00:13:06.550
And I can remember
each week, Mr. Coleman

00:13:06.550 --> 00:13:11.950
would give me back my
scrawly essay with wonderful,

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:15.300
I always look forward
to reading your writing.

00:13:15.300 --> 00:13:18.880
And then his illegible
signature in red ink.

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:24.440
If Mr. Coleman had not written
those comments on my essay

00:13:24.440 --> 00:13:26.790
when I was 14, I
don't think I would

00:13:26.790 --> 00:13:31.070
have had the energy
to write eight books.

00:13:31.070 --> 00:13:33.280
That's what I would
call inspired certainty.

00:13:33.280 --> 00:13:36.315
It can happen to you with a
grandparent, with a parent.

00:13:36.315 --> 00:13:38.357
It Could, happen to you
with a school teacher.

00:13:38.357 --> 00:13:40.690
It could happen to you today
in your life with a mentor,

00:13:40.690 --> 00:13:43.970
with a coach, someone
who is willing to see

00:13:43.970 --> 00:13:48.435
beyond the conditioned
reflexes that you have to life,

00:13:48.435 --> 00:13:52.010
many of which, for most
of us, are limiting.

00:13:52.010 --> 00:13:56.410
Many of the conditioned reflexes
are messages telling us,

00:13:56.410 --> 00:13:57.680
I can't do it.

00:13:57.680 --> 00:13:58.720
Who's going to listen.

00:13:58.720 --> 00:14:00.220
It's not possible.

00:14:00.220 --> 00:14:01.680
Who am I to do it any way?

00:14:01.680 --> 00:14:04.210
You know what I mean?

00:14:04.210 --> 00:14:05.880
Obviously that's a
rare thing at Google.

00:14:05.880 --> 00:14:09.400
But anyway, it's the
rest of the humanity.

00:14:09.400 --> 00:14:11.820
Many people suffer
from those repeating

00:14:11.820 --> 00:14:15.130
thoughts which
keeps genius at bay.

00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:17.730
Inspired certainty is
the first component,

00:14:17.730 --> 00:14:22.080
which is why the advent
of coaching beyond sports

00:14:22.080 --> 00:14:25.460
in the last 20 years--
if you go back 20 years,

00:14:25.460 --> 00:14:28.910
coaching only existed
in the relationship

00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:33.990
we understand coaching to
be in a sports context.

00:14:33.990 --> 00:14:41.480
The bursting out of coaching
beyond the context of sports

00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:45.610
into the rest of life has
allowed a huge acceleration

00:14:45.610 --> 00:14:48.120
in people being able to
bring forth a genius,

00:14:48.120 --> 00:14:52.470
because somebody else being
able to look right into you

00:14:52.470 --> 00:14:57.830
and to see what is possible is
a huge accelerator to the gifts

00:14:57.830 --> 00:15:02.640
that you were born to give in
your lifetime actually being

00:15:02.640 --> 00:15:05.480
made manifest.

00:15:05.480 --> 00:15:07.350
The second key, which
I'm actually not going

00:15:07.350 --> 00:15:09.349
to spend much time on
today, because it has more

00:15:09.349 --> 00:15:12.581
to do with coaching than really
what we're speaking about here.

00:15:12.581 --> 00:15:13.705
It has to do with presence.

00:15:18.990 --> 00:15:22.240
Learning, at least
in moments, how

00:15:22.240 --> 00:15:26.100
to show up where
you already are is

00:15:26.100 --> 00:15:31.970
a huge key to the
unfolding of your gifts.

00:15:31.970 --> 00:15:36.430
We put an incredible emphasis,
all of us, on the things

00:15:36.430 --> 00:15:42.940
that we say, the things that
we do, the accomplishments we

00:15:42.940 --> 00:15:45.540
can check off on to do list.

00:15:45.540 --> 00:15:52.380
But actually, what I've noticed
from studying highly, highly

00:15:52.380 --> 00:15:55.650
creative, successful,
genius people

00:15:55.650 --> 00:15:59.260
and from coaching people,
the way that you show up,

00:15:59.260 --> 00:16:02.280
the presence with
which you arrive

00:16:02.280 --> 00:16:04.800
into each situation
in your life is

00:16:04.800 --> 00:16:11.070
more of a factor in genius
than simply the things you

00:16:11.070 --> 00:16:12.375
accomplish.

00:16:12.375 --> 00:16:13.750
I'm going to skate
over that one.

00:16:13.750 --> 00:16:16.260
If you want to know
more about any of these,

00:16:16.260 --> 00:16:18.330
they're all seven
of these principles

00:16:18.330 --> 00:16:21.675
are very thoroughly mapped
out in the book that's

00:16:21.675 --> 00:16:23.920
at the back of the room.

00:16:23.920 --> 00:16:26.860
But the third principle
of cultivating genius,

00:16:26.860 --> 00:16:30.530
in my opinion, is
the most important.

00:16:30.530 --> 00:16:35.280
It's the component which,
if you can tap into it,

00:16:35.280 --> 00:16:38.700
make it actual yourself,
it's the closest thing

00:16:38.700 --> 00:16:42.495
I know to a genius guarantee.

00:16:46.869 --> 00:16:47.535
What was it now?

00:16:51.780 --> 00:16:54.450
The most important
key to bringing forth

00:16:54.450 --> 00:16:55.960
genius that I'm
aware of, which is

00:16:55.960 --> 00:16:58.490
why I emphasize it so much
in the coaching method

00:16:58.490 --> 00:17:04.000
that we teach, is
the possibility

00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:10.760
to effectively tap into the
dimension of yourself which

00:17:10.760 --> 00:17:16.280
is beyond conditioned
thought and reactive feeling.

00:17:16.280 --> 00:17:18.869
We could call that awakening.

00:17:18.869 --> 00:17:23.390
A nice little catch all word
for that what I'm describing

00:17:23.390 --> 00:17:24.300
is awakening.

00:17:24.300 --> 00:17:29.260
Awakening means that the
attention shifts deeper

00:17:29.260 --> 00:17:34.320
than where thoughts
play, deeper than where

00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:39.040
reactive emotions happen,
deeper than identification

00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:43.250
with the body into
a recognition of who

00:17:43.250 --> 00:17:47.270
or what is actually
experiencing this moment.

00:17:49.780 --> 00:17:52.200
Traditionally, that
has been thought

00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:56.140
of as the domain of mystics.

00:17:56.140 --> 00:17:57.490
It's thought of as mysticism.

00:17:57.490 --> 00:17:59.580
That's what the word
mysticism means,

00:17:59.580 --> 00:18:03.410
is shifting consciousness
to discover the place where

00:18:03.410 --> 00:18:09.710
you no longer exist as a
separate, localized point.

00:18:09.710 --> 00:18:13.575
But you still exist as
consciousness without limits.

00:18:18.340 --> 00:18:20.690
I'm curious to know before
we go more deeply into this,

00:18:20.690 --> 00:18:23.849
how many people feel you
recognize what I'm talking

00:18:23.849 --> 00:18:25.140
about from your own experience?

00:18:25.140 --> 00:18:26.720
You've had a taste
at least of that.

00:18:26.720 --> 00:18:27.700
Great.

00:18:27.700 --> 00:18:28.900
It's a sign of the times.

00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:33.630
I've been teaching in this way
for 25 years on this subject.

00:18:33.630 --> 00:18:37.550
25 years ago, even if I
went to a group of people

00:18:37.550 --> 00:18:42.100
who were predictably
going to say yes,

00:18:42.100 --> 00:18:45.460
spiritually-oriented people,
very few hands would go up

00:18:45.460 --> 00:18:48.350
saying, yes I know what you
mean from direct experience.

00:18:48.350 --> 00:18:51.290
People would say,
I've read about it.

00:18:51.290 --> 00:18:55.110
I've sat with a teacher
who could emanate it.

00:18:55.110 --> 00:18:58.020
But very few people 25
years ago would say,

00:18:58.020 --> 00:19:00.410
I know what you mean
from direct experience.

00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:05.060
Today, it's becoming almost
commonplace, which is actually

00:19:05.060 --> 00:19:10.610
even bigger news for the future
of humanity than breakthroughs

00:19:10.610 --> 00:19:12.810
in medicine or technology.

00:19:12.810 --> 00:19:17.360
The fact that we're having
these shifts in consciousness,

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:23.300
the likes of which we have no
evidence of in our history,

00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:26.480
is extraordinarily
hopeful good news,

00:19:26.480 --> 00:19:29.750
extraordinarily optimistic news.

00:19:29.750 --> 00:19:34.510
So let's experiment a little
bit here right now together.

00:19:34.510 --> 00:19:40.630
What we mean by
awakening to the degree

00:19:40.630 --> 00:19:43.420
that the word means
anything, it always

00:19:43.420 --> 00:19:49.150
points to this very moment now.

00:19:49.150 --> 00:19:53.070
Awakening in the way that
I want to reference it here

00:19:53.070 --> 00:19:57.320
is never about
anything in the future,

00:19:57.320 --> 00:19:59.690
never about anything
that someone else

00:19:59.690 --> 00:20:01.530
has that you could get.

00:20:01.530 --> 00:20:05.580
It's always simply a
returning the attention

00:20:05.580 --> 00:20:08.310
to what was already here
underneath the thoughts

00:20:08.310 --> 00:20:12.370
and feelings, but was
easily overlooked.

00:20:12.370 --> 00:20:14.110
So you don't need to
meditate right now.

00:20:14.110 --> 00:20:15.550
You don't need to
close your eyes

00:20:15.550 --> 00:20:17.620
or sit cross legged or anything.

00:20:17.620 --> 00:20:20.345
We can just stay
relaxed and as we are.

00:20:20.345 --> 00:20:22.230
But let's just take
a moment together

00:20:22.230 --> 00:20:28.240
to recognize that
in this moment,

00:20:28.240 --> 00:20:33.398
you are hearing the sound
of this voice, all right.

00:20:33.398 --> 00:20:36.880
It's definitely
true for everybody.

00:20:36.880 --> 00:20:41.270
You're hearing the sound
of this English accent.

00:20:41.270 --> 00:20:46.070
And you might be able to say
the words, I hear the voice.

00:20:46.070 --> 00:20:47.750
People say sentences like that.

00:20:47.750 --> 00:20:49.650
I hear the guy's voice.

00:20:49.650 --> 00:20:50.480
Who could say that?

00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:51.470
I hear the voice.

00:20:51.470 --> 00:20:53.025
You could say that's
true right now.

00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:58.670
Equally, you can see the
movement of this body standing

00:20:58.670 --> 00:20:59.170
here.

00:20:59.170 --> 00:21:01.517
You can see the
movement of the hand.

00:21:01.517 --> 00:21:03.100
How many people could
say that's true?

00:21:03.100 --> 00:21:04.360
I see the hand.

00:21:06.970 --> 00:21:11.710
So already in our experience,
without any consciousness

00:21:11.710 --> 00:21:15.530
technology being employed,
already in our experience,

00:21:15.530 --> 00:21:21.740
it's perfectly true that the
sounds are being heard already.

00:21:21.740 --> 00:21:25.370
The movement of the form
is being seen already,

00:21:25.370 --> 00:21:30.355
and in the same way,
sensations in the body

00:21:30.355 --> 00:21:34.530
are being felt already
perfectly in this moment.

00:21:34.530 --> 00:21:37.240
There's no need to
achieve any higher stake.

00:21:37.240 --> 00:21:39.730
It's already completely here.

00:21:39.730 --> 00:21:46.620
Seeing, feeling, hearing--
already completely here.

00:21:46.620 --> 00:21:48.360
So we know what is the sound.

00:21:48.360 --> 00:21:51.760
It's this English voice.

00:21:51.760 --> 00:21:53.410
We know what is the hearing.

00:21:53.410 --> 00:21:57.760
It's the movement of the sound
waves vibrating on the eardrum,

00:21:57.760 --> 00:22:01.780
activating the little
nerve in there.

00:22:01.780 --> 00:22:04.280
As you can see, I know
as much about neurology

00:22:04.280 --> 00:22:05.640
as I do about to physics.

00:22:05.640 --> 00:22:07.760
But anyway, it does
stuff in the brain.

00:22:07.760 --> 00:22:10.210
But still, none of
that explains what

00:22:10.210 --> 00:22:15.480
we mean when we say
I. I hear the sound.

00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:19.290
Now when you say I hear the
sound, most people honestly,

00:22:19.290 --> 00:22:24.590
they're not really subjectively
referring to the brain.

00:22:24.590 --> 00:22:30.842
Because you could actually
equally say, my brain.

00:22:30.842 --> 00:22:32.550
You could say, I went
to have a CAT scan.

00:22:32.550 --> 00:22:35.440
I saw a picture of my brain.

00:22:35.440 --> 00:22:41.330
So when we refer to ourselves
as I, or we say me or my,

00:22:41.330 --> 00:22:44.980
it's actually-- if you're
just innocent about it,

00:22:44.980 --> 00:22:47.950
it's not really referring
to any part of the body,

00:22:47.950 --> 00:22:50.540
including the brain
or the nervous system.

00:22:50.540 --> 00:22:54.650
It's referring to something
which, for most people,

00:22:54.650 --> 00:22:56.800
is inadequately explored.

00:22:56.800 --> 00:22:58.510
Would you agree?

00:22:58.510 --> 00:23:01.360
It's been given less attention
then it could be given,

00:23:01.360 --> 00:23:05.300
which is strange since we
use the word are I, or me,

00:23:05.300 --> 00:23:08.250
or mine more than any
other word in the day.

00:23:08.250 --> 00:23:11.560
It's strange that it
gets a little attention.

00:23:11.560 --> 00:23:12.690
But here it is.

00:23:12.690 --> 00:23:16.160
In this moment,
here in this room,

00:23:16.160 --> 00:23:23.970
you could say I hear the
sound, I see the movement,

00:23:23.970 --> 00:23:26.050
I feel the sensations
in the body.

00:23:29.050 --> 00:23:30.170
So let's experiment.

00:23:30.170 --> 00:23:33.200
Let's just shift the attention
in a very innocent way.

00:23:33.200 --> 00:23:36.370
Let's just shift the
attention towards that.

00:23:36.370 --> 00:23:38.410
It's non-localized,
so it's going

00:23:38.410 --> 00:23:41.060
to be a little bit
of an experiment

00:23:41.060 --> 00:23:44.540
to shift the attention
towards that which

00:23:44.540 --> 00:23:49.880
is hearing, and
seeing, and feeling.

00:23:49.880 --> 00:23:52.190
It's already here.

00:23:52.190 --> 00:23:54.120
It's already completely here.

00:23:54.120 --> 00:24:00.740
It's what you call me,
only usually the attention

00:24:00.740 --> 00:24:05.260
is Velcro-ing onto the movement
of thought and feeling.

00:24:05.260 --> 00:24:09.530
So what happens when
the attention just

00:24:09.530 --> 00:24:15.780
begins to turn itself towards
this which we call I or me.

00:24:15.780 --> 00:24:16.610
What happens?

00:24:16.610 --> 00:24:20.610
It may just be a tiniest
perfume at the beginning.

00:24:20.610 --> 00:24:24.250
But what begins
to reveal itself?

00:24:24.250 --> 00:24:24.920
Tell me.

00:24:28.890 --> 00:24:33.060
When you ask this question, who
is hearing in this moment, who

00:24:33.060 --> 00:24:36.975
is seeing, who is feeling,
what do you discover?

