In fact, you could
say conversely

00:28:47.120 --> 00:28:50.760
if we don't have access to the
dimension of ourselves, what

00:28:50.760 --> 00:28:52.300
do we have access to?

00:28:52.300 --> 00:28:56.140
We have access to thoughts
and feelings, right.

00:28:56.140 --> 00:28:58.720
We have access to repeating
thoughts and feelings which

00:28:58.720 --> 00:29:02.620
are almost, without
exception, conditioned,

00:29:02.620 --> 00:29:06.020
borrowed from our
culture, from our parents,

00:29:06.020 --> 00:29:09.310
from religion, from teachers.

00:29:09.310 --> 00:29:11.400
The thought machine
is really only

00:29:11.400 --> 00:29:14.360
capable of
regurgitating what it's

00:29:14.360 --> 00:29:16.070
received into
another form, which

00:29:16.070 --> 00:29:20.830
is why so much art, so much
technology is imitative,

00:29:20.830 --> 00:29:24.480
imitating something that
somebody else conceived.

00:29:24.480 --> 00:29:28.250
When you drop into the dimension
of yourself which is free,

00:29:28.250 --> 00:29:34.270
it allows for impulses to arise
which have never arisen before.

00:29:34.270 --> 00:29:36.525
There are so many stories
if you investigate.

00:29:40.120 --> 00:29:45.260
In so many fields, the
leaders, the founding fathers

00:29:45.260 --> 00:29:49.150
of this country, they were
all-- the great majority of them

00:29:49.150 --> 00:29:51.760
anyway, were mystics.

00:29:51.760 --> 00:29:56.580
They were exploring the
mysticism of Masonry.

00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:05.450
You'll find in the writings
of Benjamin Franklin

00:30:05.450 --> 00:30:09.130
many references to
this the importance

00:30:09.130 --> 00:30:11.920
of being able to
drop out of the me

00:30:11.920 --> 00:30:19.190
into the dimension where there
is boundaryless consciousness.

00:30:19.190 --> 00:30:22.760
If we had longer, we could
explore the great leaders

00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:25.530
in almost every field and
find the same pattern.

00:30:25.530 --> 00:30:31.230
Having access to infinity is
the way in which impulses arise.

00:30:31.230 --> 00:30:34.280
Now, we could talk on
each of these memes,

00:30:34.280 --> 00:30:35.400
we could talk for hours.

00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:39.000
But let's move on to the
next important meme, which

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:43.210
has to do with blocks
and conditioning.

00:30:43.210 --> 00:30:48.270
I think I read
today on Google, I

00:30:48.270 --> 00:30:53.820
found the statistics for
how much sperm a human male

00:30:53.820 --> 00:30:58.220
produces in his lifetime is
like 525 billion sperm, right.

00:30:58.220 --> 00:31:00.710
But how many of those
sperm actually make

00:31:00.710 --> 00:31:05.110
it to become an embodied
expression of what

00:31:05.110 --> 00:31:06.730
each sperm have the potential?

00:31:06.730 --> 00:31:08.520
It's like a few.

00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:13.850
Most of the sperm that
comes out of a man

00:31:13.850 --> 00:31:18.500
never makes it to become
anything embodied or expressed.

00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:25.650
In the same way, I would suggest
to you for all of humanity,

00:31:25.650 --> 00:31:27.610
for all seven
billion human beings,

00:31:27.610 --> 00:31:29.930
impulses are arising
all the time.

00:31:29.930 --> 00:31:31.560
When you first wake
up in the morning

00:31:31.560 --> 00:31:33.310
and you're still in a
more spacious state,

00:31:33.310 --> 00:31:37.410
impulses, little ideas,
are arising all the time.

00:31:37.410 --> 00:31:40.700
How many of those
impulses actually become

00:31:40.700 --> 00:31:45.460
manifest as something that
can radically contribution

00:31:45.460 --> 00:31:49.690
to and shift the
destiny of humanity,

00:31:49.690 --> 00:31:51.235
or least people around you.

00:31:51.235 --> 00:31:52.730
You see the theme?

00:31:52.730 --> 00:31:55.310
The majority of impulsive,
creative impulses

00:31:55.310 --> 00:31:58.510
that arise in you,
they meet immediately

00:31:58.510 --> 00:32:05.529
with not birth control,
but creativity control.

00:32:05.529 --> 00:32:11.180
And creativity control
means hard set ideas

00:32:11.180 --> 00:32:15.620
along the lines of,
I'm not good enough.

00:32:15.620 --> 00:32:17.370
I don't have enough time.

00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:18.540
Who am I?

00:32:18.540 --> 00:32:20.249
Nobody listens to me.

00:32:20.249 --> 00:32:21.290
Does this sound familiar?

00:32:23.860 --> 00:32:25.320
Nobody would try it anyway.

00:32:25.320 --> 00:32:27.280
It's too crazy.

00:32:27.280 --> 00:32:30.230
I don't have enough money.

00:32:30.230 --> 00:32:34.440
We could continue the
whole day cataloging

00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:37.100
the mechanism of
the conditioned mind

00:32:37.100 --> 00:32:39.750
that's suppresses
pure creative impulse.

00:32:44.130 --> 00:32:50.420
We could map it very easily if
we sat together in a workshop.

00:32:50.420 --> 00:32:52.200
We could easily map
this out, and we'd

00:32:52.200 --> 00:32:54.890
find almost any
conditioned thought

00:32:54.890 --> 00:32:57.120
that anybody came up with.

00:32:57.120 --> 00:32:59.430
Most of the rest
of them would say,

00:32:59.430 --> 00:33:01.980
would agree that that's a
conditioned thought for them

00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:03.050
too.

00:33:03.050 --> 00:33:05.770
The conditioned mind
is entirely programmed.

00:33:05.770 --> 00:33:12.020
It operates along
principles that

00:33:12.020 --> 00:33:15.150
are the same for
almost everybody.

00:33:15.150 --> 00:33:17.830
So what's necessary in
order to bring forth

00:33:17.830 --> 00:33:20.150
genius in a way
that's reliable is

00:33:20.150 --> 00:33:26.490
to have technology to be able
to address those blocks which

00:33:26.490 --> 00:33:30.870
interfere with the arising
of creative impulse.

00:33:30.870 --> 00:33:32.940
So how are you going to do that?

00:33:32.940 --> 00:33:36.820
The difficulty is that
you don't consciously

00:33:36.820 --> 00:33:41.042
choose those thoughts
when they arise, right?

00:33:41.042 --> 00:33:42.500
A thought like I'm
not good enough,

00:33:42.500 --> 00:33:44.080
you don't have the
idea of, now I'm

00:33:44.080 --> 00:33:45.954
going to have an I'm
not good enough thought.

00:33:45.954 --> 00:33:46.920
Just a minute.

00:33:46.920 --> 00:33:48.870
There it is.

00:33:48.870 --> 00:33:50.120
You don't do that.

00:33:50.120 --> 00:33:52.490
It comes on its own.

00:33:52.490 --> 00:33:55.780
But when a thought like
I'm not good enough,

00:33:55.780 --> 00:33:58.600
or there's not enough money,
or nobody listens to me, when

00:33:58.600 --> 00:34:03.730
it arises to block creativity,
generally what relationship

00:34:03.730 --> 00:34:08.235
instinctively do we
form with that thought?

00:34:08.235 --> 00:34:09.139
AUDIENCE: Aversion.

00:34:09.139 --> 00:34:10.139
ARJUNA ARDAGH: Aversion.

00:34:10.139 --> 00:34:10.650
Who said it?

00:34:10.650 --> 00:34:11.149
Aversion.

00:34:11.149 --> 00:34:12.550
It's totally true, isn't it?

00:34:12.550 --> 00:34:16.130
Whenever these creativity
blocking thoughts

00:34:16.130 --> 00:34:18.389
arise, and there
are lots of them,

00:34:18.389 --> 00:34:20.480
the immediate
response is aversion.

00:34:23.320 --> 00:34:24.810
So we've been experimenting.

00:34:24.810 --> 00:34:27.030
I teach a method called
awakening coaching.

00:34:27.030 --> 00:34:30.040
We've been experimenting
over decades

00:34:30.040 --> 00:34:36.659
to discover what
can we do to unplug

00:34:36.659 --> 00:34:40.610
the power from that
conditioned thinking,

00:34:40.610 --> 00:34:44.909
so that creativity has more
opportunity to express itself.

00:34:44.909 --> 00:34:46.889
And the key actually
is what you just said.

00:34:46.889 --> 00:34:50.100
The key is aversion.

00:34:50.100 --> 00:34:54.510
When a thought arises, and
it's allowed to pass through,

00:34:54.510 --> 00:34:57.500
which is quite rare,
it actually just

00:34:57.500 --> 00:35:03.270
has almost no effect on the
way you behave in your life.

00:35:06.420 --> 00:35:08.750
You start to discover these
thoughts are like a mouse

00:35:08.750 --> 00:35:12.090
with a megaphone,
making a lot of noise,

00:35:12.090 --> 00:35:15.530
but with very little
inherent power.

00:35:15.530 --> 00:35:18.260
So the key is to
have a technology,

00:35:18.260 --> 00:35:20.630
not that gets rid of the
thoughts-- that's actually,

00:35:20.630 --> 00:35:25.000
in my opinion, that's the
rabbit hole that we often

00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:25.710
try to go down.

00:35:25.710 --> 00:35:27.590
We try to get rid of
negative thoughts,

00:35:27.590 --> 00:35:30.220
or make them into
positive thoughts.

00:35:30.220 --> 00:35:33.320
But the more energy you
give to a thought form,

00:35:33.320 --> 00:35:36.310
the more you turn up the
volume on the megaphone.

00:35:36.310 --> 00:35:40.100
The key as you suggested
is to have a technology,

00:35:40.100 --> 00:35:42.080
not to get rid of
the thought form,

00:35:42.080 --> 00:35:45.170
but to relax the resistance.

00:35:45.170 --> 00:35:48.010
So that's the meme.

00:35:48.010 --> 00:35:52.080
That's the meme, is to recognize
that any thought form, when

00:35:52.080 --> 00:35:55.340
resisted, becomes real.

00:35:55.340 --> 00:35:57.990
The more you push against
it, the more real it becomes.

00:35:57.990 --> 00:36:00.230
Any thought form
when unresisted,

00:36:00.230 --> 00:36:03.840
and unresisting is not just
a matter of not resisting.

00:36:03.840 --> 00:36:07.710
Unresisting is a creative act.

00:36:07.710 --> 00:36:11.330
Any thought form when
unresisted actually,

00:36:11.330 --> 00:36:15.400
instead of becoming
bigger, it dissipates.

00:36:15.400 --> 00:36:16.630
It becomes humorous.

00:36:16.630 --> 00:36:21.410
It passes through,
leaving you free to give

00:36:21.410 --> 00:36:23.962
the gift you were born to give.

00:36:23.962 --> 00:36:25.420
Again, each of
these memes we could

00:36:25.420 --> 00:36:27.830
explore in much greater
depth, but let's move

00:36:27.830 --> 00:36:31.785
on to the next meme, which
has to do with practice.

00:36:35.830 --> 00:36:39.120
We don't really need
practice to have awakening.

00:36:39.120 --> 00:36:43.090
Awakening is always, in this
moment, simply the willingness

00:36:43.090 --> 00:36:44.900
to return attention
to what is here.

00:36:44.900 --> 00:36:49.440
We do need practice
to be able to live

00:36:49.440 --> 00:36:52.980
that creative source
in day to day life.

00:36:52.980 --> 00:36:57.020
Not only do we have conditioned
thoughts, conditioned beliefs,

00:36:57.020 --> 00:36:59.170
all of us, we have
conditioned ways

00:36:59.170 --> 00:37:04.212
of behaving, which are held
in place through homeostasis.

00:37:04.212 --> 00:37:07.670
What that means is, you show
up at work in a certain way.

00:37:07.670 --> 00:37:08.450
Maybe you show up.

00:37:08.450 --> 00:37:11.730
And you're the guy who was
always a little bit shy.

00:37:11.730 --> 00:37:13.990
or you're somebody
who's really--

00:37:13.990 --> 00:37:16.090
and everybody's used to
you behaving like that.

00:37:16.090 --> 00:37:18.680
So if the shy guy shows
up one day and goes like,

00:37:18.680 --> 00:37:21.250
yeah, everyone's going
to be completely shocked.

00:37:21.250 --> 00:37:23.180
Not because it's a
strange way to behave,

00:37:23.180 --> 00:37:26.692
it's an unexpected way
for that person to behave.

00:37:26.692 --> 00:37:28.257
You see what I mean?

00:37:28.257 --> 00:37:30.840
So as soon as you enter into a
relationship with other people,

00:37:30.840 --> 00:37:34.620
or with an environment, you
enter into an unspoken contract

00:37:34.620 --> 00:37:41.550
of homeostasis, which means
that in order to free up genius,

00:37:41.550 --> 00:37:44.740
we need tailor-made practice.

00:37:44.740 --> 00:37:46.970
One size fits all
practice won't work.

00:37:46.970 --> 00:37:48.720
Because it just
becomes another habit.

00:37:48.720 --> 00:37:52.640
We need tailor-made
practice to antidote,

00:37:52.640 --> 00:37:57.240
to exaggerate, to make
humorous the habits which

00:37:57.240 --> 00:37:58.509
have governed our lives.

00:37:58.509 --> 00:38:00.550
I'm going to give you a
couple of quick examples.

00:38:00.550 --> 00:38:03.099
Again, each of these
topics is a huge thing

00:38:03.099 --> 00:38:04.140
to explore in more depth.

00:38:04.140 --> 00:38:08.080
I'll give you a very quick
example of a university

00:38:08.080 --> 00:38:11.030
professor I worked
with a few years ago

00:38:11.030 --> 00:38:13.540
who wanted to write a book.

00:38:13.540 --> 00:38:16.890
Now the habit he
developed over years

00:38:16.890 --> 00:38:21.150
was of being a very serious,
respectable university

00:38:21.150 --> 00:38:21.650
professor.

00:38:21.650 --> 00:38:23.350
He was-- nobody laughed at him.

00:38:23.350 --> 00:38:25.620
And it was to do with his
childhood, his conditioning.

00:38:25.620 --> 00:38:28.010
It was important to him to
be taken very seriously.

00:38:28.010 --> 00:38:30.700
But you can imagine when
he tried to write a book,

00:38:30.700 --> 00:38:35.750
it became very quickly an
academic, very sturgid book.

00:38:35.750 --> 00:38:38.310
So we have to find a
tailor-made practice for him,

00:38:38.310 --> 00:38:41.960
not a practice that is going to
be the same for everybody, just

00:38:41.960 --> 00:38:43.490
everybody meditate
for 20 minutes.

00:38:43.490 --> 00:38:45.080
Or everyone do
this yoga posture.

00:38:45.080 --> 00:38:47.470
We had to find the
perfect practice for him,

00:38:47.470 --> 00:38:52.480
like a homeopathic medicine,
that would free up his genius.

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:56.060
And this is perhaps one of
the most important gifts

00:38:56.060 --> 00:38:59.020
that a good coach or a good
mentor can bring to you,

00:38:59.020 --> 00:39:01.480
is to find tailor-made practice.

00:39:01.480 --> 00:39:03.230
So this was the practice
we found for him.

00:39:03.230 --> 00:39:05.110
It's a random example.

00:39:05.110 --> 00:39:07.680
He had to give lectures
at the university

00:39:07.680 --> 00:39:13.100
in the huge auditorium
with 500, 800 seats.

00:39:13.100 --> 00:39:14.834
So I said to him,
next time you're

00:39:14.834 --> 00:39:17.000
going to give one of these
really big lectures where

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:18.520
he was the serious
professor, I said

00:39:18.520 --> 00:39:24.110
before you go to give the
lecture, go to a costume store

00:39:24.110 --> 00:39:29.104
and buy a cat's tail--
they sell tail there--

00:39:29.104 --> 00:39:30.770
and attach it to the
back of your pants.

00:39:33.690 --> 00:39:34.910
So of course he came in.

00:39:34.910 --> 00:39:36.201
He started to give the lecture.

00:39:36.201 --> 00:39:37.750
Everything was normal.

00:39:37.750 --> 00:39:39.287
He was the serious professor.

00:39:39.287 --> 00:39:41.120
He quickly forgot about
the tail, of course.

00:39:41.120 --> 00:39:42.970
And then he had to turn
around at some point

00:39:42.970 --> 00:39:46.240
to write something on the
whiteboard behind him,

00:39:46.240 --> 00:39:48.740
revealing the tail.

00:39:48.740 --> 00:39:51.016
Well, it was just a little
murmur at the beginning.

00:39:51.016 --> 00:39:53.390
People bringing out-- quietly
bring out their cell phone,

00:39:53.390 --> 00:39:56.430
taking a picture.

00:39:56.430 --> 00:40:00.530
It only took that one lecture,
one hour lecture of him wearing

00:40:00.530 --> 00:40:03.940
a tail to dismantle
the homeostasis of him

00:40:03.940 --> 00:40:06.227
being the serious professor.

00:40:06.227 --> 00:40:08.060
After that, he could
walk around the campus.

00:40:08.060 --> 00:40:11.040
Everybody would give him a wink
or a wave, because they knew.

00:40:11.040 --> 00:40:13.410
That's the guy
who wore the tail.

00:40:13.410 --> 00:40:15.270
That's just a silly example.

00:40:15.270 --> 00:40:18.090
There are an infinite
number of examples

00:40:18.090 --> 00:40:21.420
of where the right practice
for the right person

00:40:21.420 --> 00:40:25.770
can disrupt the homeostasis
enough that it frees up,

00:40:25.770 --> 00:40:27.960
not a new way of
behaving-- you see,

00:40:27.960 --> 00:40:29.500
that would be
another conditioning.

00:40:29.500 --> 00:40:33.650
It frees up a return
to innocence, a return

00:40:33.650 --> 00:40:40.100
to childlike play, which is
the environment in which genius

00:40:40.100 --> 00:40:40.725
can happen.

00:40:44.120 --> 00:40:48.440
The sixth meme I want to
briefly touch on today

00:40:48.440 --> 00:40:51.310
is the recognition
of unique gift.

00:40:51.310 --> 00:40:55.010
The recognition as we
drop more and more deeply

00:40:55.010 --> 00:40:58.040
into infinite consciousness,
into consciousness

00:40:58.040 --> 00:41:00.820
without limits, as
we free up blocks

00:41:00.820 --> 00:41:05.260
through removing resistance, as
we find tailor-made practices

00:41:05.260 --> 00:41:09.070
that can disrupt
the encrusted habits

00:41:09.070 --> 00:41:12.170
and allow you to live more
freely, more spontaneously.

00:41:12.170 --> 00:41:17.740
What reveals itself after
a while is the astounding

00:41:17.740 --> 00:41:20.140
recognition that just as
each of us in this room

00:41:20.140 --> 00:41:24.740
has a unique fingerprint, just
as each of us in this room

00:41:24.740 --> 00:41:28.250
has a unique face that is very
rarely confused with anyone

00:41:28.250 --> 00:41:31.750
else's face, so each
person in this room,

00:41:31.750 --> 00:41:35.430
and each person that
you know in your life,

00:41:35.430 --> 00:41:41.840
has a unique gift to
give to the world.

00:41:41.840 --> 00:41:43.530
But I hesitate to
say unique gift,

00:41:43.530 --> 00:41:46.400
because I don't mean
necessarily that there's

00:41:46.400 --> 00:41:50.570
a particular product that
they were born to invent,

00:41:50.570 --> 00:41:56.530
or anything is manifest is that
I mean that each person has

00:41:56.530 --> 00:41:58.850
a unique, energetic flavor.

00:42:01.670 --> 00:42:05.010
A flavor which, if it's not
fully given through you,

00:42:05.010 --> 00:42:07.980
it will never be given.

00:42:07.980 --> 00:42:16.135
Just like if you don't put your
thumb on the thumbprint thingy

00:42:16.135 --> 00:42:17.885
and give your thumb
print, that thumbprint

00:42:17.885 --> 00:42:19.960
will never get recorded,
because nobody else has

00:42:19.960 --> 00:42:22.460
got the same thumbprint as you.

00:42:22.460 --> 00:42:25.780
If the gift which is
inherently your genius

00:42:25.780 --> 00:42:28.820
is not delivered into the
world in your lifetime,

00:42:28.820 --> 00:42:30.710
it simply is not given.

00:42:30.710 --> 00:42:34.860
It remains unmanifest,
which sounds sad,

00:42:34.860 --> 00:42:39.620
but unfortunately it's still
more or less the default

00:42:39.620 --> 00:42:41.550
setting for humanity.

00:42:41.550 --> 00:42:43.970
Most gifts go on giving.

00:42:43.970 --> 00:42:45.530
In small ways, they get given.

00:42:45.530 --> 00:42:48.510
But I know from coaching
people, majority

00:42:48.510 --> 00:42:51.510
of people I work with, they
know that what they really

00:42:51.510 --> 00:42:53.945
came to give is still held back.

00:42:53.945 --> 00:42:54.820
Does that make sense?

00:42:57.500 --> 00:43:01.180
We are rapidly, because of
the way society is changing,

00:43:01.180 --> 00:43:07.797
because of the democratization
of genius with YouTube,

00:43:07.797 --> 00:43:09.130
which is owned by which company?

00:43:09.130 --> 00:43:10.790
I've forgotten.

00:43:10.790 --> 00:43:13.190
Because of technologies
like YouTube,

00:43:13.190 --> 00:43:16.330
anybody can unlock their
genius and share it

00:43:16.330 --> 00:43:19.810
with the world
very, very easily.

00:43:19.810 --> 00:43:23.220
The unique gift means
a reliable technology

00:43:23.220 --> 00:43:28.490
to be able to tap into the
energetic flavor, which

00:43:28.490 --> 00:43:32.180
is uniquely yours, and to
find the right match for it

